	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First of all, the &quot;bouncing&quot; effect is pure BS. I've played 3 mages, and a wizard too, which also have bolts, and I have never ever seen this. Also, I have never heard one single &quot;reliable&quot; source mention this. This spell is available in ALL mage guilds, along with the other level 8 spells.<BR>
And yes, the spell CAN damage something you haven't targetted if it gets in the way. NOT pc's though (maybe on PvP servers, but on all other servers, it is IMPOSSIBLE to damage pc's unless duelling or in Arena)<BR>
All level 8 spells cost around 4.5 pp, slightly depending on charisma and faction.<BR>
While this spell is great in some cases, I would usually prefer shock of blades, since it is slightly more mana efficient and doesn't require free line of sight. As a rule of thumb: If your pet can easily survive long enough to drop the enemy with shock of blades, use that. If you need to drop the enemy ASAP, use bolt.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
