				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Arendar - if you still dont understand what a black (or white or blue or red) creature is what is being referred to is when you use the consider command (right click or press c on a creature) you get a message telling you if the creature is higher or lower level than you.  &quot;Santa Claus regards you dubiously...what do you want on your tombstone&quot; telling you its way above your level...always written in red letters.  This is a red creature. Or &quot;Its probably a safe fight&quot; in green...this is a green creature, which is far below your level and worthless for exp.  Blue is a little below you, white or black (depending on which size viewscreen yuo have up using f10) is equal level to you, yellow slightly higher level than you.  Blue through yellow soloing and yellow or red if grouped are best for exp.  Some reds are too strong to fight even if grouped.
				</font>
